{"action":"patch","name":"hermes-agent","new_string":"If Hermes is being run from the `/opt/hermes` source checkout and `hermes` is not on PATH, use `.venv/bin/python ./hermes ...` from the repo root. If the endpoint returns 401 and the CLI asks for a token/header, rerun with `--auth oauth` rather than entering an API key. In headless/WSL environments the OAuth flow may print a URL and the browser may fail to reach `localhost:<port>` because the callback listener is inside WSL. Keep the login process running, have the user paste the full `http://localhost:<port>/callback?...` redirect URL, then bridge it with `curl` to `http://127.0.0.1:<port>/callback?...` from WSL. Do not probe the callback URL first: the listener is one-shot. If the default login times out before the user can paste the redirect, use the long-timeout probe recipe in `references/composio-mcp.md`. Reload MCP tools or start a new session after OAuth.

More detail: `references/composio-mcp.md`.","old_string":"If Hermes is being run from the `/opt/hermes` source checkout and `hermes` is not on PATH, use `.venv/bin/python ./hermes ...` from the repo root. If the endpoint returns 401 and the CLI asks for a token/header, rerun with `--auth oauth` rather than entering an API key. In headless environments the OAuth flow may print a URL and time out; save the config anyway if prompted, then have the user complete `hermes mcp login composio` in a browser-capable environment. Reload MCP tools or start a new session after OAuth.

